**NOTES:**
The iOS port was not properly updated, and may not compile without few manual changes. This is a known issue and hopefully will be resolved in following minor updates (e.g. 3.5.1). The main reason is that it still relies on older Allegro version and requires old hacks to work.

This release contains many bug fixes, both critical and minor, accumulated for the last year. For the actual list of changes see [Changes.txt](https://github.com/adventuregamestudio/ags/blob/release-3.4.3/Changes.txt).

Apart from that, for MS Windows we no longer distribute "No-MP3" version of the engine and also removed the ancient "Demo Quest" game source from installer package.

